00:14:11.562 --> 00:14:12.756
and they're dynamically generated.

00:14:12.756 --> 00:14:13.787
They'll work you all the way up.

00:14:13.787 --> 00:14:15.084
Right now, they go through about algebra.

00:14:15.084 --> 00:14:16.756
The videos go well beyond that,

00:14:16.756 --> 00:14:18.486
but the exercise I want
them to go through calculus

00:14:18.486 --> 00:14:21.796
and chemistry, and
those keep building out.

00:14:21.796 --> 00:14:23.176
We collect data on everything.

00:14:23.176 --> 00:14:24.341
we know what videos you've watched,

00:14:24.341 --> 00:14:25.388
when you've watched the videos,

00:14:25.388 --> 00:14:27.750
what exercises you've watched.

00:14:27.750 --> 00:14:31.000
We'll do heuristics on when you're stuck,

00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:33.468
and then what I think would
kind of complete the picture

00:14:33.468 --> 00:14:34.900
of a virtual school is,

00:14:35.500 --> 00:14:38.127
leverage the community to do
actual peer-to-peer instruction,

00:14:38.127 --> 00:14:41.060
so if I know that Andrew is having trouble

00:14:41.060 --> 00:14:42.372
with negative exponents

00:14:42.372 --> 00:14:45.939
